// The equipment definition contains the probability to get an item between 0 and 100
// These definition are used for phalanx initial equipment and alien equipment.
// In the following, we describe the selection of weapons for aliens, but the same
// procedure is used for initial equipment of phalanx soldiers.
//
// Alien weapon assignment procedure, more or less (see inv_shared.c):
// For each alien, pick the following:
// 1. Get a primary weapon:
// 1a. Get a primary weapon:
//    A primary weapon is randomly picked in all primary weapon available. The sum of the
//    probability for all primary weapon must not exceed 100. If this sum is below 100 --
//    let's say 80 -- there is 20 % proability that the alien has no primary weapon.
// 1b. Select an ammo:
//    If several ammo types are available for the selected weapon, ammo is randomly chosen
//    with the relative probability given by the last 2 numbers. If there is at least one ammo type
//    in the equipment definition, you will have an ammo.
//    Example: ammo1 125	ammo2 250. 
//             ammo1 has 25/(25+50)*100 = 33 % probability to be selected.
//             ammo2 has 50/(25+50)*100 = 67% probability to be selected.
// 1c. get the following number of ammo for the selected ammo type:
//    there is a probability given by the last 2 numbers to get one ammo, plus
//    the first number of the probability number.
//    Example : with previous values, 
//            you'll have 25% to have 2 ammo1 (else only 1 ammo1)
//            you'll have 50% to have 3 ammo2 (else only 2 ammo1)
//    This number is the number of ammo alien will have in the backpack (weapon is already loaded)
//
// 2. Get a secondary weapon with reload (sidearms):
//    The procedure is the same as for primary weapon.
//    If alien got a primary weapon in first step with damage type 'particle' or 'normal', then
//       all probabilities are divided by 2 (therefore, you have a maximum 50 % probabilty to have
//       a secondary weapon)
//    If alien got no primary weapon, but got a secondary weapon, there is 30 % that he gets a second one.
//
// 3. If alien has no weapon at this stage, there is 40% chance that we go back to 2.
//    to increase the probability to get a secondary weapon.
//
// 4. Get misc items and secondary weapons without reload: (that includes kerrblades or plasblade)
//    The probability is used in the same way as for ammos. Therefore, you can use proability greater
//    than 100 to get several grenades.
//
// 5. If alien has no primary nor secondary weapon at this stage, there is 40% chance
//    that we go back to 4 to increase number of misc items.
//
// 6. If alien has no weapon at this stage, the most expensive secondary weapon without reload (ie knife)
//    will be selected.
//
// 6. Get an armour:
//    Same procedure as for primary weapons. The probability to get an armour is increased if alien has
//    no primary weapon.
//
// For a given weapon category (except blades), the total probability should never exceed 100.
// Note that a weapon can be added only if alien has still room to get it. An alien with primary and
//    secondary weapon won't prabably get any Kerr Blade.
//
// there are 2 types of alien equipment:
// alien_workersS or alien_soldiersS
//    alien_workers is used for harvest, recon, building and supply missions.
//    alien_soliders is used for all other mission categories.
//    S is any string (used to specify the equipment definition)
//    For a given stage, all equipment definition can be chosen with the same proability.
//    For each alien equipment, you must specifiy mininterest and maxinterest: the lower
//    and upper value of overall alieninterest that can use this equipment definition.
//    Equipment used will be picked randomly between all definition fitting overallinterest.
//    Note that all equipment definitions must have different names.


